College: Sri Ranganathar Institute of Engineering and Technology, Coimbatore
Approval: (AICTE) All India Council of Technical Education
Eligiblity:
1. For First Year-
Candidates of HSC (Academic) and Other Equivalent Examinations.
Community - Minimum average marks in Maths+Physics+Chemistry.
1. General Category - 50% [300/600]
2. Backward Class including Backward Class Muslim - 45% [270/600]
3. MBC and DNC - 40% [240/600]
4. SC/SCA/ST - 40% [240/600]
Engineering Cut-Off Marks = (Maths/2)+(Physics/4)+(Chemistry/4)
B. Candidates of HSC (Vocational).
Community - Minimum average marks in any one of Related Subjects (Maths or Physics or Chemistry), Vocational Theory and Practicals put together
1. General Category - 50%
2. Backward Class including Backward Class Muslim - 45%
3. MBC and DNC - 40%
4. SC/SCA/ST - 40%
2. For Direct Second Year (Lateral Entry)-
B.Sc.,/Diploma holders are admitted directly in second year B.E / B.Tech. Courses.
Community - Minimum average marks in the Pre-Final and Final semesters put together or Final year.
1. General Category - 55%
2. Backward Class including Backward Class Muslim - 50%
3. MBC and DNC - 45%
4. SC/SCA/ST - 40%
Course_Detail: This is a full time four year course affiliated to Anna University, Chennai and approved by AICTE.

College: Sreepathy Institute of Management and Technology, Palakkad
Approval: (AICTE) All India Council of Technical Education
Eligiblity:
Candidates who have passed Higher Secondary Examination, Kerala, or Examinations recognized as equivalent thereto, with 50% marks in Mathematics separately, and 50 % marks in Mathematics, Physics and Chemistry put together are eligible for admission. However candidates who have passed Higher Secondary Examination, Kerala, or Examinations recognized as equivalent thereto, with 45% marks in Mathematics, Physics and Chemistry put together are eligible for admission under Management Quota in Private Self Financing Engineering Colleges/Government Controlled Self Financing Engineering Colleges. In case, the candidate has not studied Chemistry, the marks obtained in Computer Science shall be considered. In case, the candidate has not studied Chemistry and Computer Science, the marks obtained in
Biotechnology shall be considered. In case, the candidate has not studied Chemistry, Computer Science and Biotechnology, the marks obtained in Biology shall be considered. The marks as shown in the mark list of the Board of Examination obtained from the respective Higher Secondary Board shall be considered for academic eligibility.
Under Lateral Entry
Candidates who have passed Diploma in Engineering awarded by the State Board of Technical Education or Equivalent after undergoing regular course of three years in an approved institution are eligible for admission. All admissions will be as per the rank list prepared by the Joint Controller of Technical Examinations, Thiruvananthapuram. Maximum age at the time of admission will be 28 years.
Course_Detail: Bachelor of Technology in Civil Engineering is a full-time four-year course degree offered by APJ Abdul Kalam Technological University, Thiruvananthapuram and approved by AICTE.

College: Spintronic Technology and Advance Research, Bhubaneswar
Approval: (AICTE) All India Council of Technical Education
Eligiblity:
Passed or appearing in 2016, 10+2 examination of Council of Higher Secondary Education, Odisha or equivalent with Physics and Mathematics as compulsory subjects along with one of the subjects from Chemistry / Biotechnology / Biology/ Electronics / Computer Science / Information Technology/ Geology / Statics. The candidate should have passed individual subject and must have obtained at least 45% marks (40% in case of candidate belonging to SC/ST category) in the above subjects taken together and must have qualified in OJEE-2016 or JEE MAIN-2016.
5% seats are available over and above of the total intake under Tution Fee Waiver (TFW) scheme, whose parents annual income is less than Rs.4.50 lacs.
For Lateral Entry:
20% seats of total intake and carry forward vacant seats of last year (2015-16) are open for 2nd year admission for Diploma holders and B.Sc/+3 Science students. They must have OJEE-2016 rank for the purpose.
Passed or appearing in 2015/16, in diploma examination in Engineering from State Council of Technical Education and Training (SCTE&VT;), Odisha or equivalent with at least 45% marks (40% in case of candidates belonging to SC/ST category) in appropriate branch of Engineering / Technology.

College: Shri Someshwar Shikshan Prasarak Mandal, Someshwar Engineering College, Pune
Approval: (AICTE) All India Council of Technical Education
Eligiblity:
Candidate should be an Indian National and should have passed the HSC (Std.XII) examination of Maharashtra State Board of Secondary and Higher Secondary Education or its equivalent examination with subjects English, Physics, Mathematics and Chemistry/Biotechnology /Biology/ Technical Vocational subject
Secured minimum 50 % marks (minimum 45 % marks, in case of Backward class categories and Persons with Disability candidates belonging to Maharashtra State only) in the subjects Physics, Mathematics and Chemistry/Biotechnology/Biology/ Technical Vocational subject added together
Obtained a positive Composite score* i.e., score obtained after adding 50% of JEE (Main) 2015 (Paper 1) marks percentile and 50% of Standard XII (Board or Equivalent Examination) Physics, Chemistry and Mathematics marks percentile.
For Lateral Entry: The Candidate must be an Indian National and should have passed Post-SSC or Post-HSC Diploma Course in Engineering/Technology with at least 45.00 % marks (40.00 % marks in case of candidates of backward class categories belonging only to Maharashtra State) in appropriate branch of Engineering / Technology from an AICTE approved Institution with English as the medium of instruction at Diploma level
Candidate Passing SSC (Std.X)/HSC (Std.XII) Examination or any other Equivalent Examination from a Recognized School / College in Maharashtra State
Diploma Examination / B. Sc Examiniation as specified in rule 2.1 from a Recognized Institution in Maharashtra State.
Candidate is Domiciled/Born in the State of Maharashtra.
Course_Detail: Bachelor of Technology in Civil Engineering is a full-time four-year course affiliated to Savitribai Phule Pune University, Pune and approved by AICTE.

College: Jaywant College of Engineering and Management, Sangli
Approval: (AICTE) All India Council of Technical Education
Eligiblity:
For the candidate of Maharashtra state in addition to educational qualification as specified in the Para "Entry Requirement", candidates should require to apply for MH-CET and should secure non zero score to eligible for admission for state quota (65%) seats through Centralized Admission Process (CAP).
For the candidate outside Maharashtra state, in addition to educational qualification as specified in the Para "Entry Requirement", candidates are require to appear and qualify in All India Engineering Entrance Examination (AIEEE) conducted by CBSE, New Delhi for that academic year & should be eligible for admission against this 15% reserve seats.
For the candidate wishing admission under Management Quota Candidates from Maharashtra state as well as outside Maharashtra State having educational qualification as specified in the Para "Entry Requirement" are eligible for management quota (20%) seats provided that they have to appear for MH-CET conducted by the competent authority or conducted by agency (if any) including association of all private colleges approved by Pravesh Niyantran Samity. However they are required to apply separately to management of the institute for these seats.
For the Diploma Holder candidates.
After admitting candidates fulfilling the eligibility criteria mention at Para (1, 2. and 3) above, if the vacancies still exist after the cut off date declared by the concern Government authority, the principal may admit diploma holders who have passed the Diploma course in engineering/ technology with minimum 50% marks & medium of instruction as English from polytechnics affiliated to MSBTE or AICTE, approved autonomous Polytechnics in Maharashtra state (for Maharashtra state candidates) or such polytechnics situated in or outside Maharashtra state (for outside the Maharashtra state candidate) such admissions are also as per merit of candidates applied for the particular un-aided college.
Course_Detail: Bachelor of Technology in Civil Engineering is a full-time four-year course affiliated to Shivaji University, Kolhapur and approved by AICTE.

College: Shanti Niketan College of Engineering, Hisar
Approval: (AICTE) All India Council of Technical Education
Eligiblity:
1. For First year - Passed 10+2 examination with Physics and Mathematics as compulsory subjects along with one of the Chemistry / Biotechnology/Biology/ Technical Vocational subject Obtained at least 45% marks (40% in case of candidate belonging to reserved category) in the above subjects taken together.
2. For Lateral Entry to second year -
A. Passed diploma examination from an AICTE approved Institution with at least 45% marks (40% in case of candidates belonging to reserved category) in appropriate branch of Engineering/Technology.
B. Passed B.Sc Degree from a recognized University as defined by UGC, with at least 45% marks ( 40% in case of candidates belonging to reserved category) and passed XII, standard with mathematics as a subject.
C. Provided that in case of students belonging to B.Sc. Stream, shall clear the subjects of Engineering Graphics/ Engineering Drawing and Engineering Mechanics of the first year Engineering Program along with the second year subjects.
D. Provided further that, the students belonging to B.Sc. Stream shall be considered only after filling the supernumerary seats in this category with students belonging to the Diploma Stream.
E. Provided further that students, who have passed Diploma in Engineering & Technology from an AICTE approved Institution or B.Sc Degree from a recognized University as defined by UGC, shall also be eligible for admission to the first year Engineering Degree Course subject to vacancies in the first year class in case the vacancies at lateral entry are exhausted. However the admissions shall be based strictly on the eligibility criteria as mention in A,B,C,D and E above.

College: Priyadarshini Indira Gandhi College of Engineering, Nagpur
Approval: (AICTE) All India Council of Technical Education
Eligiblity:
For Maharashtra State Candidate: Candidate should be an Indian National and should have passed the HSC (Std.XII) examination of Maharashtra State Board of Secondary and Higher Secondary Education or its equivalent examination with subjects English, Physics, Mathematics and any of Chemistry or Biology or Vocational Subject.
AND
Secured minimum total 50 % marks (minimum total 45% marks in case of candidates of Backward class categories and Persons with Disability belonging only to Maharashtra State) in the subjects Physics, Mathematics AND any of Chemistry or Biology or Vocational Subject added together AND Obtained a non zero score in subjects Physics, Chemistry and Mathematics added together at JEE 2015.
For Direct Admission to Second Year-
Educational Qualification:
The candidate must be an Indian National and should have passed Post-SSC or
Post-HSC Diploma course in Engineering/Technology of the Maharashtra State
Board of Technical Education (MSBTE) or autonomous institute to which autonomy has been granted by the state or Maharashtra or diploma recognized as equivalent to the diploma awarded by MSBTE with English medium and at least 50.00% marks (45.00% marks in case of candidates of backward class categories belonging only to Maharashtra State) in appropriate branch of Engineering/Technology from an AICTE approved Institution with English as the medium of instruction at Diploma level.
OR
The candidate must be an Indian National and should have passed B.Sc. Degree from a UGC/Association of Indian Universities recognized University with at least 50.00% marks (45.00% marks in case of candidates of Backward class categories belonging only to Maharashtra State) and passed XII standard examination with Mathematics as the subject and with English as the medium of instruction at B.Sc. level.
Note: The students belonging to B.Sc. Stream shall only be considered after filling the seats in this category. Students belonging to Diploma stream and students belonging to B.Sc. Stream are required to pass subjects of Engineering Graphics/Engineering Drawing and Engineering Mechanics of the First year Engineering program along with the second year subjects.
Course_Detail: This is a full time four year course affiliated to Rashtrasant Tukadoji Maharaj Nagpur University, Nagpur and approved by AICTE.

Board of Technical Education (MSBTE) or autonomous institute to which autonomy has been granted by the state or Maharashtra or diploma recognized as equivalent to the diploma awarded by MSBTE with English medium and at least 50.00% marks (45.00% marks in case of candidates of backward class categories belonging only to Maharashtra State) in appropriate branch of Engineering/Technology from an AICTE approved Institution with English as the medium of instruction at Diploma level.

The candidate must be an Indian National and should have passed B.Sc. Degree from a UGC/Association of Indian Universities recognized University with at least 50.00% marks (45.00% marks in case of candidates of Backward class categories belonging only to Maharashtra State) and passed XII standard examination with Mathematics as the subject and with English as the medium of instruction at B.Sc. level.

Stream are required to pass subjects of Engineering Graphics/Engineering Drawing and Engineering Mechanics of the First year Engineering program along with the second year subjects.

College: Namdeorao Poreddiwar College of Engineering and Technology, Gadchiroli
Approval: (AICTE) All India Council of Technical Education
Eligiblity: Maharashtra State Candidate - 1. Candidate should be an Indian National and should have passed the HSC (Std.XII) examination of Maharashtra State Board of Secondary and Higher Secondary Education or its equivalent examination with subjects English, Physics, Mathematics and Chemistry/Biotechnology /Biology/ Technical Vocational subject. 2. Secured minimum 50 % marks (minimum 45 % marks, in case of Backward class categories and Persons with Disability candidates belonging to Maharashtra State only) in the subjects Physics, Mathematics and Chemistry/Biotechnology/Biology/ Technical Vocational subject added together. 3. Obtained a positive Composite score (The details for calculating positive Composite score shall be notified separately by DTE, Maharashtra state) i.e., marks obtained after adding 50% of JEE (Main) (Paper 1) marks and 50% of normalized Standard XII (Board or Equivalent Examination) marks in Physics, Chemistry and Mathematics. Eligibility Criteria for All India Candidates - 1. Candidate should be an Indian National and should have passed the HSC (Std.XII) examination of Maharashtra State Board of Secondary and Higher Secondary Education or its equivalent examination with subjects English, Physics, Mathematics and Chemistry/Biotechnology /Biology/ Technical Vocational subject. 2. Secured minimum 50 % marks (minimum 45 % marks, in case of Backward class categories and Persons with Disability candidates belonging to Maharashtra State only) in the subjects Physics, Mathematics and Chemistry/Biotechnology/Biology/ Technical Vocational subject added together 3. Obtained All India Rank in JEE (Main) (Paper 1) given by CBSE. DIRECT 2nd YEAR ADMISSION (DSE) - The Candidate must be an Indian National and should have passed Post-SSC or Post-HSC Diploma Course in Engineering/Technology with at least 50.00 % marks (45.00 % marks in case of candidates of backward class categories belonging only to Maharashtra State) in appropriate branch of Engineering/Technology from an AICTE approved Institution with English as the medium of instruction at Diploma level.

College: Muslim Association College of Engineering, Thiruvananthapuram
Approval: (AICTE) All India Council of Technical Education
Eligiblity:
Eligibility will be subject to the rules and regulations of APJ Abdul Kalam Technological University (KTU) /AICTE/Govt.
1. The candidate shall be an Indian National.
2. The candidate should have studied in the graduate course in an institution approved by the AICTE/Deemed Universities and must have scored minimum of 60% marks in Graduate Degree examination in the appropriate branch of engineering.
3. For SC/ST candidates a pass in the Engineering Degree course is sufficient.
4. For SEBC students, a minimum of 54% aggregate marks in the Engineering Degree examination is mandatory.
5. Candidates who have degrees awarded from other Universities shall submit Eligibility Certificate as well as Migration Certificate at the time of admission.
6. Eligibility as per relevant stream
7. Candidates, who have passed AMIE/AMIETE Examinations and satisfying the following conditions, are eligible for admission. They must have valid GATE score. A minimum of 55% marks for section B in AMIE/AMIETE examination. Minimum three years of Professional experience in the field of Specialization after acquiring the qualifying degree.
8. Candidates who have appeared for the final semester examination can also apply, provided he/she has passed all the subjects up to and including the 6th semester exam. Selection of such candidates shall be subject to the production of qualifying degree on the time of admission. Those who are having valid GATE score and who are waiting for the result of the supplementary examinations of the above or previous semesters can also apply. Confirmation of admission of such candidates shall be subject to the production of qualifying degree –satisfying clauses (1) to (5) as applicable on or before the date notified by DTE, Kerala
9. Admission shall normally be restricted to those with valid GATE score.
10. In case seats remain vacant due to lack of candidates with valid GATE score, candidates from Kerala State without valid GATE score will be considered against such vacancies. If seats are still remaining vacant, candidates from other states will be considered for admission.
Course_Detail: Master of Technology (M.Tech.) in Electrical Power Systems is a Post Graduate program of technical field. The duration of this course is 2 years with 4 semesters and Course approved by AICTE.

College: Maharani Girls Engineering College, Jaipur
Approval: (AICTE) All India Council of Technical Education
Eligiblity:
1. Candidates must have taken at least five subjects in class 12th/ qualifying examination in order to be eligible for eligible to be admitted through REAP. The candidates who have taken four subjects are not permitted to participate in REAP and if such candidates appear in REAP by furnishing wrong information, their admission/allotment shall be cancelled.
2. Passed 10+2 examination with Physics and Mathematics as compulsory subjects along with one of the Chemistry/Biotechnology/Biology/ Technical Vocational subject. Obtained at least 45% marks (40% in case of candidate belonging to reserved category) in each of the subjects.
3. Above mentioned condition in the subjects combination as given above taken together, in the final examination of 10+2 (Class XII) of Board of Secondary Education, Rajasthan or any other examination recognized equivalent thereto by Board of Secondary Education, Rajasthan / Central Board of secondary Education (CBSE).
4. Candidates with JEE marks, and who have passed 10+2 examination with above mentioned criterion in 2016 or 2015 only are eligible.
5. Only those candidates shall be eligible who have passed in each subject of above combination and fulfills the minimum academic qualification as mentioned above latest on 15 June.
Age : Only those candidates whose date of birth falls on or after October 01, 1991 are eligible. However, in the case of Scheduled Caste (SC), Scheduled Tribe (SD and Person with Disability (PwD) candidates, upper age limit is relaxed by 5 years, i.e. SC, ST and PwD candidates who were born on or after October 01, 1986 are eligible. Date of birth as recorded in the Secondary Education mark sheet / certificate only will be taken as authentic.
Medical Fitness : A candidate desirous of admission to Engineering Colleges will have to deposit the Medical Fitness Certificate at the time of reporting in the allotted institution on the prescribed form certified by a Medical Officer of the Government of Rajasthan or a Registered Medical Practitioner as per medical standards laid down below:
Height:Not less than 1.5 m for male candidates and not less than 1.4 m for female candidates.
Weight:Not less than 41 kg. for male candidates and 37 kg for female candidates (Approximately).
Chest Measurement: Not less than 69 cm with satisfactory limits of expansion and contraction (for male candidates only).
Heart & Lungs:No abnormality.
Hernia, Hydrocele, Piles etc.:Presence of any of these will be a temporary disqualification to be rectified before joining the courses of study.
Vision: Normal. Where defective, it must be corrected to 6/9 in the better eye and 6/12 in the worse eye. Eyes should be free from congenital and other diseases. In case of admission to Engineering courses, the candidates must be free from colour blindness (inability to dis yogesh shat between principal colours) also .
Hearing: Normal. Where defective, it must be
Speech:Speech: Normal.
Course_Detail: Bachelor of Technology in Civil Engineering is four-year duration full-time course affiliated to Rajasthan Technical University, Kota and approved by All India Council for Technical Education (AICTE).

The candidates who have taken four subjects are not permitted to participate in REAP and if such candidates appear in REAP by furnishing wrong information, their admission/allotment shall be cancelled.
2. Passed 10+2 examination with Physics and Mathematics as compulsory subjects along with one of the Chemistry/Biotechnology/Biology/ Technical Vocational subject. Obtained at least 45% marks (40% in case of candidate belonging to reserved category) in each of the subjects.
3. Above mentioned condition in the subjects combination as given above taken together, in the final examination of 10+2 (Class XII) of Board of Secondary Education, Rajasthan or any other examination recognized equivalent thereto by Board of Secondary Education, Rajasthan / Central Board of secondary Education (CBSE).
4. Candidates with JEE marks, and who have passed 10+2 examination with above mentioned criterion in 2016 or 2015 only are eligible.
5. Only those candidates shall be eligible who have passed in each subject of above combination and fulfills the minimum academic qualification as mentioned above latest on 15 June.
Age : Only those candidates whose date of birth falls on or after October 01, 1991 are eligible. However, in the case of Scheduled Caste (SC), Scheduled Tribe (SD and Person with Disability (PwD) candidates, upper age limit is relaxed by 5 years, i.e. SC, ST and PwD candidates who were born on or after October 01, 1986 are eligible. Date of birth as recorded in the Secondary Education mark sheet / certificate only will be taken as authentic.
Medical Fitness : A candidate desirous of admission to Engineering Colleges will have to deposit the Medical Fitness Certificate at the time of reporting in the allotted institution on the prescribed form certified by a Medical Officer of the Government of Rajasthan or a Registered Medical Practitioner as per medical standards laid down below:
Height:Not less than 1.5 m for male candidates and not less than 1.4 m for female candidates.
Weight:Not less than 41 kg. for male candidates and 37 kg for female candidates (Approximately).
Chest Measurement: Not less than 69 cm with satisfactory limits of expansion and contraction (for male candidates only).
Heart & Lungs:No abnormality.
Hernia, Hydrocele, Piles etc.:Presence of any of these will be a temporary disqualification to be rectified before joining the courses of study.
Vision: Normal. Where defective, it must be corrected to 6/9 in the better eye and 6/12 in the worse eye. Eyes should be free from congenital and other diseases. In case of admission to Engineering courses, the candidates must be free from colour blindness (inability to dis yogesh shat between principal colours) also .
Hearing: Normal. Where defective, it must be
Speech:Speech: Normal.

College: Lourdes Matha College of Science and Technology, Thiruvananthapuram
Approval: (AICTE) All India Council of Technical Education
Eligiblity:
Nationality-
Applicants must be citizens of India
Academic Requirements-
Candidates who have passed Higher Secondary Examination, Kerala, or Examinations recognized as equivalent thereto, with 50% marks in Mathematics separately, and 50% marks in Mathematics, Physics, and Chemistry put together are eligible for admission. However, Candidates who have passed Higher Secondary Examination, Kerala, or Examinations recognized as equivalent thereto, with 45% marks in Mathematics separately and 45% marks in Maths, Physics, and Chemistry put together are eligible for admission under Management Quota in Private Self Financing Engineering Colleges.
For applicants belonging to SEBC category with a total annual family income not exceeding 6 lakhs, relaxation of 5% in qualifying marks is permitted. For SC/ST applicants, a pass in the examination is sufficient.
Age-
Applicants should have completed 17 years of age.
Entrance Exam-
Candidates should qualify in the Engineering Entrance Examination conducted by the
Commissioner for Entrance Examination, Govt of Kerala.

Chemistry/Biology/Computer Science.
Minimum Academic Qualifications for B. Tech Should be a pass with at least 50% marks (45% in case of candidate belonging to reserved category i.e. SC category) in the above subjects taken together.

Eligiblity:
Other Communities (OC):
(Communities other than BC / MBC / SC / ST) Pass in 12th standard or equivalent with an aggregate of at least 55% marks in Mathematics, Physics & Chemistry
Backward Class Community (BC) of Tamil Nadu:
Pass in 12th standard or equivalent with an aggregate of at least 50% marks in Mathematics, Physics & Chemistry. The candidate should produce the Community Certificate duly signed by the Tahsildar
Most Backward Class Community (MBC) of Tamil Nadu:
Pass in 12th standard or equivalent with an aggregate of at least 45% marks in Mathematics, Physics & Chemistry. The candidate should produce the Community Certificate duly signed by the Tahsildar
SC/ST Community of Tamil Nadu:
Mere pass in 12th standard or equivalent with Mathematics, Physics & Chemistry. The Candidate should produce the Community Certificate duly signed by the Tahsildar. Note : Candidates from other states irrespective of their community are considered as OC (Other Community)
LATERAL ENTRY - DIRECT II YEAR B.E./B.TECH
Other Communities:
(Communities other than BC / MBC / SC / ST) Pass in 3 year Diploma examination conducted by the State Board of Technical Education of respective states in the relevant subjects with a minimum of 55% marks in the final year examination. Pass in any recognized bachelor’s degree in Science of minimum 3 years duration with Mathematics as a subject
Backward Class Community of Tamil Nadu:
An aggregate of 50% marks in the final year diploma examination / Final yearB.Sc.degree course
Most Backward Class Community of Tamil Nadu:
An aggregate of 45% marks in the final year diploma examination / final yearB.Sc.degree course
SC/ST Candidates of Tamil Nadu:
Merit pass is enough in Diploma Course / B.Sc. Degree course.

College: Jagannath Institute of Engineering and Technology, Cuttack
Approval: (AICTE) All India Council of Technical Education
Eligiblity:
The student must have passed or appeared 10+2 examination from CHSE, Odisha or Equivalent board with Physics & Mathematics as compulsory subjects along with one of the subjects from Chemistry / Biotechnology / Biology / Information Technology / Geology / Statistics. The candidate should have Passed individual subject and must have obtained at least 45% marks (40% in case of candidate belonging to SC/ST category) in the above subjects taken together. There is no age limit to appear at OJEE for admission into Engineering & Technology courses.
Lateral Entry (Applicable to native of Odisha)
I. The student must have passed or appeared in three year Diploma examination (two Year in case of Lateral entry Diploma) in Engineering from State Council of Technical Education and Training (SCTE&VT;), Odisha or from an AICTE approved Institute / from a recognized University as defined by UGC with at least 45% marks (40% in case of candidate belonging to SC/ST category) in appropriate branch of Engineering / Technology.
II. The student must have passed or appeared in the Bachelor's Degree examination of three years duration in Science from any University of Odisha or from a recognized University as defined by UGC, with at least 45% marks (40% in case of candidate belonging to SC/ST category) and must have passed 10+2 examination with Mathematics as a subject. Further even though a student from this stream is admitted to second year course, he / she has to clear the subjects of Engineering Drawing and Engineering Mechanics of first year engineering program along with second year subjects. The student has to submit the Permanent Resident Certificate (Appendix - I) at the time of counselling.
III. Final results of Diploma examination must be available by the date of counselling. Candidates, whose results are not available on the day of counselling, will not be allowed to participate in the counselling. Candidates have to submit the Permanent Nativity Certificate (Appendix - I) at the time of counselling.

College: Gandhi Academy of Technology and Engineering, Berhampur
Approval: (AICTE) All India Council of Technical Education
Eligiblity:
1. He / She should have passed +2 Science or XII standard with Physics and Mathematics as compulsory subjects along with any one of the following subjects from Chemistry / Biotechnology / Biology / Electronics / Information Technology / Statistics/Computer Science. The candidate should have passed in individual subject and must have obtained at least 45% (40% for the candidates belonging to ST/SC category) in the above subjects taken together.
2. He / She should have possessed a valid rank card of OJEE/JEE (main).
3. He / She should have opted our college name as his/her first choice & mentioned the disciplines of engineering available for admission into B.Tech. Programme during the time of online choice fill up at Nodal Centers.
For Lateral Entry : (i) For Direct Admission to third semester degree Course -
1. He / She should have passed 3 years diploma in Engineering in appropriate branch of Engineering/ Technology from State Council of Technical Education and Training (SCTE & VT) or equivalent with a minimum of 45% (40% for the candidates belonging to ST/SC category).
2. He / She should have possessed a valid rank card of OJEE.
3. He / She should have opted our college name as his/her first choice & mentioned the disciplines of engineering available for admission into B.Tech. Programme during the time of online choice fill up at Nodal Centers.
(ii) For Admission to 2nd year Degree Courses in Engineering & Technology under Lateral entry scheme for B.Sc./+3 Science Students:
1. He / She should have passed Bachelors Degree of Examination of 3 years duration in Science in the relevant field from any University of Odisha or equivalent recognized university as defined by UGC with a minimum of 45% (40% for the candidates belonging to ST/SC category) in aggregate in the qualifying examination and must have passed XII standard with mathematics as a subject.
2. He / She should have possessed a valid rank card of OJEE.
3. He / She should have opted our college name as his/her first choice & mentioned the disciplines of engineering available for admission into B.Tech. Programme during the time of online choice fill up at Nodal Centers.
Course_Detail: Bachelor of Technology in Civil Engineering is four-year duration full-time course affiliated to Biju Patnaik University of Technology, Rourkela and approved by All India Council for Technical Education (AICTE).

College: Apex Institute of Technology, Rampur
Approval: (AICTE) All India Council of Technical Education
Eligiblity:
By merit of candidates in qualifying (10+2) examination.In this category, the candidates must have secured a minimum of 50% (45% for SC/ST) marks (or the minimum percentage of marks set by the AICTE/UPTU, Lucknow) in total in the required subject combination: (Physics+Maths+Chemistry/Biotechnology/Computer Science/Biology) without grace marks.
For Lateral Entry: 50% marks in Engineering Diploma or 50% marks in B.Sc with Mathematics as one of the subject (or the minimum percentage of marks set by the AICTE/UPTU, Lucknow)
Admission through UPSEE conducted by Uttar Pradesh Technical University, Lucknow and subsequent counselling.
The vacant seats after counselling shall be filled by the institute strictly on merit basis.
Course_Detail: Bachelor of Technology in Computer Science and Engineering is a full-time four-year course affiliated to Dr APJ Abdul Kalam Technical University, Lucknow and approved by AICTE.

College: Hindustan Institute of Technology and Management, Ambala

E. Provided that in case of students belonging to B. Sc. Stream, shall clear the subjects of Engineering Graphics I Engineering Drawing and Engineering Mechanics of the first year engineering program along with the second year subjects.
1. Provided further that, the students belonging to B. Sc. Stream shall be considered only after filling the supernumerary seats in this category with students belonging to the Diploma stream.
2. Provided further that students, who have passed Diploma in Engineering & Technology from a AICTE approved institution or B.Sc. Degree from a recognized University as defined by UGC, shall also be eligible for admission to the first year engineering Degree courses subject to vacancies in the first year class in case the vacancies for lateral entry are exhausted. However the admission shall be based strictly on the eligibility criteria as mentioned.
Course_Detail: B.Tech Civil Engineering is a full-time four years duration course Affiliated to Kurukshetra University, Kurukshetra Approved by AICTE.
